<chapter id="runpylith">
  <title>Running PyLith</title>

  <!-- SECTION +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
  <section>
    <title>Input Files</title>
    <para>
      PyLith gets its input from a variety of files. Most of these are
      associated with different kinds of boundary conditions. As a
      result only six are required.
    </para>

    <!-- SECTION +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
    <section>
      <title>Required Input Files</title>
      <para>
        The required input files define the finite-element mesh,
        boundary conditions, time step information, output of state
        variables, and material properties.
      </para>
      <variablelist>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><filename>xx.coord</filename></term>
	  <listitem>
	    <para>
              Coordinates of finite-element vertices.
            </para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><filename>xx.connect</filename></term>
	  <listitem>
	    <para>
              Topology of finite-element mesh.
            </para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><filename>xx.bc</filename></term>
	  <listitem>
	    <para>
              Specifies boundary conditions at nodes on external boundaries.
            </para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><filename>xx.time</filename></term>
	  <listitem>
	    <para>
              Specifies at time stepping information.
            </para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><filename>xx.statevar</filename></term>
	  <listitem>
	    <para>
              Specifies which state variables are to be output for the
              elastic and (time-dependent) viscoelastic solution.
            </para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>
	<varlistentry>
	  <term><filename>xx.prop</filename></term>
	  <listitem>
	    <para>
              Specifies properties for each material.
            </para>
	  </listitem>
	</varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
    </section>

